"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692509","Department for Education","false","2017-03-08","<p>In 2016, 2,847 institutions entered at least one pupil for at least one A-level. Of these, 1,272 institutions (45%) entered at least one pupil for an A-level in government and politics[1].</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] Derived from School Performance Tables available at</p><p><a href="https://www.compare-school-performance.service.gov.uk/download-data?currentstep=datatypes&amp;regiontype=all&amp;la=0&amp;downloadYear=2015-2016&amp;datatypes=ks5underlying" target="_blank">https://www.compare-school-performance.service.gov.uk/download-data?currentstep=datatypes&amp;regiontype=all&amp;la=0&amp;downloadYear=2015-2016&amp;datatypes=ks5underlying</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-03-08T14:56:56.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692509/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692509/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-21","Politics and Government: GCE A-level","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of post-16 education institutions entered at least one pupil for an A-level in government and politics in 2016.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","64717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692510","Department for Education","false","2017-02-24","<p>On 20 October, the department published the early years foundation stage profile (EYFSP) results for the 2015 to 2016 academic year, at national and local authority level. The EYFSP results are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016, 69.3% of children achieved a good level of development. Of the 30.7% of children who did not achieve a good level of development in 2016, the information to determine the number and proportion of those children who did not attend any funded hours of childcare, is not readily available and could only be compiled at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-24T12:53:20.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692510/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692510/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692510/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-21","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 16 January 2017 to Question 59691, of the 30.7 per cent of children who did not achieve a good level of development in 2016, how many and what proportion did not attend any funded hours of child care.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","64779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692511","Department for Education","false","2017-02-24","<p>On 20th October, the Department for Education published the early years foundation stage profile (EYFSP) results for the 2015 to 2016 academic year, at national and local authority level. The EYFSP results are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016, 69.3% of children achieved a good level of development. Of the 30.7% of children who did not achieve a good level of development in 2016, 0.015% (30 children) attended a childminder when their EYFSP was undertaken.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-24T12:50:53.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692511/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692511/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692511/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-21","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 16 January 2017 to Question 59691, of the 30.7 per cent of children who did not achieve a good level of development in 2016, how many and what proportion attended a childminder.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","64778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692512","Department for Education","false","2017-03-08","<p>The information that the honourable member requires is not routinely available in Key Stage 5 data. I have asked the statistical head of profession to review the analysis for the information requested by the honourable member. The Department plans to publish this for the first time in a statistical bulletin on Key Stage 5 attainment by characteristics, on 16 March 2017.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","64794","2017-03-08T17:23:44.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692512/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692512/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692512/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-21","Arts: GCE A-level","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students (a) eligible and (b) not eligible for free school meals have taken (i) art, (ii) music and (iii) drama A-level in each of the last six years; and what proportion of all students taking each of those A-levels those figures represent.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","64792"
