"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692615","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-27","<p>DFID’s bilateral programme in the Occupied Palestinian Territories currently funds human rights NGOs providing legal assistance to Palestinians, through a multi-donor access to justice programme implemented by UN agencies.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-02-27T16:42:49.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692615/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692615/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692615/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-21","Occupied Territories: Non-governmental Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is giving to non-governmental organisations promoting human rights in the Occupied Palestinian Territories.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","64773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692616","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-28","<p>I visited South Sudan earlier this month. During my visit, I met with Stephen Dhieu, South Sudan’s Minister for Finance and Economic Planning, and delivered a clear message: that the Government of South Sudan must bring an end to the fighting and allow humanitarian access to all areas of the country.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-02-28T16:37:44.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692616/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692616/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-21","South Sudan: Famine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with her South Sudanese counterpart on the flow of emergency aid into areas affected by the UN-declared famine in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","64807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692617","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-15","<p>Question 55553 was answered on Thursday 09 March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice recognises that as a result of process and system changes we have experienced a recent reduction in performance with regard to QWA responses. The Department has assured me that they have taken steps to rectify this, including making further process improvements.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-15T11:20:51.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692617/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692617/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692617/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when she plans to answer Question 55553, on prison sentences: Lancashire, tabled by the hon. Member for Preston on 30 November 2016; and what the reasons are for the time taken to answer that Question.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","64826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692619","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-16","<p>The £450,000 cost to the Electronic Monitoring (EM) programme represents people resources engaged in the procurement of the next generation tags. These resources have been supplied by contractors to provide expert capability and capacity to strengthen accountability and governance during the Procurement exercise. This has helped ensure that the programme remains compliant with EU regulations, meets legal obligations of fairness, transparency and openness and provides confidence and assurance in the contract award decision.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-16T12:07:52.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692619/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692619/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Electronic Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 15 February 2017 to Question 59530, if she will provide a breakdown of the £450,000 cost of procurement activity for the supplier of the new electronic monitoring tags based on satellite tracking technology.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","64827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692620","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-24","<p>The life cycle of prisons currently in planning or under construction is, for the purposes of business case development, 60 years. The performance of buildings within the existing prison estate is not measured according to life cycle, which is a more recent component of business case development. We keep the entire prison estate under review to make sure that it remains fit for purpose.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-24T14:33:20.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692620/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692620/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prisons: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many buildings within the prison estate have exceeded their intended life cycle.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","64889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692621","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-24","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-24T14:32:16.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692621/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692621/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prisons: Dogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many dog patrol officers have been employed in prisons in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","64886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692624","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-27","<p>The information requested is available in the NOMS workforce statistics section on gov.uk.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-27T14:13:34.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692624/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692624/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prison Officers: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officer posts are currently vacant in each region.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","64927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692625","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested has been provided in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year (1 June)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of full time equivalent officials</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>12.15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>10.15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>15.98</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>15.98</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>15.98</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>17.98</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>18.37</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017 - present</p></td><td><p>18.37</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Prior to 2012, ten staff worked in prison regions and were responsible for corruption, professional standards and counter-terrorism. The amount of time spent on corruption varied by region depending on local need and they have therefore not been included in the table above. From 2012, full-time regional corruption prevention managers were allocated to the Corruption Prevention unit and have been included in the above figures.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, all prisons have an identified Local Corruption Prevention Manager (LCPM), and in some cases a deputy, who develops intelligence, raises awareness of corruption prevention and supports staff to report any corruption related concerns. This role is carried out in addition to other duties they may hold in a prison and so have not been included in the figures provided.</p><p> </p><p>The vast majority of staff undertake their duties with honesty and integrity. However, the Prison Service is committed to investigating and eliminating corruption to ensure prisons remain a safe and secure environment for staff, prisoners and visitors.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-28T16:58:07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692625/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692625/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prisons: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many full-time equivalent staff in the prison service have worked on investigations into alleged corruption in prisons in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","64699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692626","Attorney General","false","2017-02-28","<p>No individual who was investigated as part of Operation Sacristy was charged with perverting the course of justice.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2017-02-28T17:16:47.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692626/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692626/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-02-21","Cleveland Police Authority: Offences against the Administration of Justice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, whether any individuals under investigation during Operation Sacristy were charged with perverting the course of justice.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","64769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692627","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-03","<p>The number of adult offenders sentenced to immediate custody, by gender, offence category and court at all courts in the North Wales police force area can be viewed in the tables as follows:-</p><p> </p><ul><li>Table 1 provides information for Mold Crown Court</li><li>Table 2 provides information for Wrexham Maelor Local Justice Area</li><li>Table 3 provides information for Flintshire Local Justice Area.</li><li>Table 4 provides information for Denbighshire Local Justice Area</li><li>Table 5 provides information for Conwy Local Justice Area</li><li>Table 6 provides information for Ynys Mon (Anglesey) Local Justice Area</li><li>Table 7 provides information for Gwynedd Local Justice Area</li></ul><p> </p><p>Magistrates’ courts data is reported by the Ministry of Justice by Local Justice area, which can contain one or more magistrates’ courts.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide equivalent information for juveniles. This is because this information, if released, could lead to identification of the individuals concerned.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-03T11:57:18.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692627/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692627/answer","PQ 64767  ANNEX.DOC","Offenders sentenced to immediate custody","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692627/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Custodial Treatment: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been given an immediate custodial sentence of less than six months in courts used by North Wales Police in North Wales by (a) gender and (b) offence in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","64767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692630","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-27","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not oversee judicial training; the Lord Chief Justice does through the Judicial College.</p><p> </p><p>The Judicial College provides awareness training of unconscious bias and the subject has been included in family law training. The Judicial College publishes the Equal Treatment Bench Book, which contains information about protected and other characteristics and includes a section on gender equality. This is publicly available at: <a href="https://www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/equal-treatment-bench-book/" target="_blank">https://www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/equal-treatment-bench-book/</a> and enables judges to be sensitive to all issues of equal treatment, and to treat people fairly in proceedings.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-02-27T16:52:33.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692630/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692630/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Judges: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will take steps to ensure that judges in family courts receive training on preventing gender bias.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","64754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692631","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-28T17:06:10.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692631/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692631/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prisons: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Assessment, Care in Custody and Teamwork assessors are employed in each public sector prison.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","64707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692632","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-27","<p>The information requested is available in the NOMS workforce statistics section on gov.uk.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-27T14:11:50.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692632/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692632/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prison Officers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) Band 3 Prison Officer job offers have been made by HM Prison Service and (b) prison officer entry level training starts have been recorded since 3 November 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","64708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692633","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-02","<p>We are committed to making prisons places of safety and reform and giving prisoners the support and treatment they need to help turn their lives around.</p><p> </p><p>All prisons have established procedures in place to identify, manage and help prisoners with mental health issues. Increased support is now available to those at risk of self-harm or suicide, especially in the first 24 hours, and we have invested in mental health awareness training for staff.</p><p> </p><p>All establishments provide The ‘Introduction to Mental Health’ which covers the factors which cause mental ill-health and the main types of disorders which offenders can display and ‘Introduction to Safer Custody’ course which are delivered locally for all prison officers.</p><p> </p><p>There is also a ‘Personality Disorder’ module within the ‘Introduction to Mental Health’ course, and the ‘Introduction to Safer Custody’ course, for Prison Officers which highlights the impact a personality disorder may have on an offender and how they can be supported. It also explains how to respond to challenging behaviour from an offender with this type of disorder. As part of the accredited Personality Disorder Knowledge and Understanding framework (PD-KUF) awareness level training is widely available to prison-based staff. Further non-accredited ‘Personality Disorder’ training is offered at prisons that host an Offender Personality Disorder treatment service.</p><p> </p><p>‘Emotional and Mental Wellbeing’ training is delivered to officers who will be working in the Young People’s Estate. This training outlines the factors which influence typical and atypical developments during adolescence and ensures learners can identify when an offender requires specialist support and referral.</p><p> </p><p>There is an ‘Enhanced Mental Health’ course which is run locally for Case Managers and Assessment Care in Custody Treatment (ACCT) Assessors only as they are the point of contact for an offender who is identified to be at risk. Within this training learners are taught to identify signs and symptoms for the various forms of mental ill-health, how to manage the offender and when it is necessary to seek help from healthcare professionals.</p><p> </p><p>For note, there are also a number of establishments who have worked with NHS trusts to commission bespoke mental health training</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-02T16:19:33.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692633/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692633/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692633/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prison Officers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will list what mental health training courses are available to prison officers who are not Assessment, Care in Custody and Teamwork assessors after those officers have completed prison officer entry level training.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","64709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692634","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-28","<p>New joiner data is publicly available in the NOMS workforce statistics section on gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p>We do not hold data on number of candidates who do not complete Prison Officer Entry Level Training each year.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-28T17:12:06.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692634/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692634/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Prison Officers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many candidates (a) started and (b) did not complete prison officer entry level training in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","64710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692637","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-02","<p>During 2014 extensive work was undertaken to transfer MoJ’s higher rate customer service lines into local rate numbers. This initiative was reported at that time and a copy of the report that was issued is attached for reference. Since that time the responsibility for these lines has been devolved to the ALBs and MOJ does not hold any information centrally, in this regard.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-03-02T11:30:32.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692637/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692637/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Ministry of Justice: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much income has been accrued to her Department from premium rate telephone lines in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","64741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692638","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-03","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service is responsible for ensuring that case outcome and sentence information, including whether the defendant was found guilty or not guilty, is sent to the police for inclusion on the Police National Computer (PNC). The average time taken to send case results to the police in the financial year 2015/16 was 1.3 working days.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice has no further involvement in Disclosure and Barring Service processes and is a matter for the Home Office.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-03-03T11:55:54.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692638/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692638/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692638/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-21","Criminal Records: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the (a) procedures and (b) timescales are by which findings of not guilty are entered into the criminal record database; and at what point a person found not guilty receives a clear Disclosure and Barring Service check.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","64746"
