"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692640","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>These questions are a matter for the Irish Government.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is my understanding that: since 1998, a number of pieces of legislation have been introduced in the Republic of Ireland including the Employment Equality Acts 1998 and 2004; the Republic of Ireland ratified the Council of Europe Framework Convention on National Minorities in 1999, and; the Irish Human Rights and Equality Commission, like the Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission, is a UN ‘A status’ accredited National Human Rights Institution, structured and operated in accordance with the Paris Principles.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","64845 ; 64846","2017-02-27T15:27:49.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692640/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692640/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692640/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-21","Belfast Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether the Republic of Ireland has implemented enhanced employment equality legislation as required by paragraph 9 of the Chapter on rights, safeguards and equality of opportunity in the Belfast Agreement of 1998.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","64844"
