"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692642","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-02-27","<p>These questions are a matter for the Irish Government.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is my understanding that: since 1998, a number of pieces of legislation have been introduced in the Republic of Ireland including the Employment Equality Acts 1998 and 2004; the Republic of Ireland ratified the Council of Europe Framework Convention on National Minorities in 1999, and; the Irish Human Rights and Equality Commission, like the Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission, is a UN ‘A status’ accredited National Human Rights Institution, structured and operated in accordance with the Paris Principles.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","64844 ; 64845","2017-02-27T15:27:49.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692642/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692642/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692642/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-02-21","Belfast Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether the Republic of Ireland has established a human rights commission with a mandate and remit equivalent to that within Northern Ireland as required by paragraph 9 of the Chapter on rights, safeguards and equality of opportunity in the Belfast Agreement of 1998.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","64846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692643","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-01","<p>Germany is one of our most important partners in the world; in trade, foreign policy and in Europe. We are working to strengthen the bilateral relationship further following the UK’s decision to leave the EU, including through high level visits, however there are no plans for President-elect Steinmeier to visit the UK in the immediate future.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-01T17:11:47.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692643/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692643/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692643/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-21","State Visits: Germany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make arrangements for an early state or official visit to the UK by the recently elected President of Germany.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","64905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692644","Department for Transport","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Government believes that pavement parking is better addressed on a local basis and powers are already available to local authorities to do so. The Department for Transport is looking at ways of improving and simplifying the process for local authorities to use these powers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-02-24T10:41:50.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692644/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692644/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/692644/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-21","Parking: Pedestrian Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to introduce legislative proposals to prevent vehicles parking on pavements.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","64875"
